==English==

===Pronounciation===
fer'klemt, fa'klemp

===Etymology===
{{Cattag2|Yiddish language|Yiddish derivations}}
''Yiddish'' or ''High German''

===Adjective===
[[Category:English adjectives]]
'''faklempt'''
# Suffering from [[neurotic]] [[symptom]]s of fear about [[imaginary]] threats.
# [[nervous]] or sweaty
# concerned and anxious
#* When little Billy got sick, his mom became '''faklempt'''.
#* The first day on the job made Bill '''faklempt'''.

